    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "annot-1cd3899fs9x3",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 810,
      "width": 734.4,
      "height": 126,
      "text": "AS-BUILT amendment 2026-07-11 (SS6.5.4 wire tier): the gateway matches the requested model against the\nthree CONFIGURED tier models. A match runs AND meters at THAT tier (FAST/WORKHORSE/EXPERT) with the\nclient's thinking/output_config preserved (a trailing '[1m]' client alias is stripped on the wire).\nAny OTHER model string keeps the historical behavior: clamp to FAST + strip reasoning params.\nMotivation: Agent-SDK subprocess traffic rides this gateway via ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL - the always-FAST\nclamp silently degraded chat/build/planner to the FAST model (strict-JSON planning starved).\nBilling impact: matched EXPERT calls meter at 0.4 vs FAST 0.02 - correct per SS6.3, ~20x costlier.",
      "originalText": "AS-BUILT amendment 2026-07-11 (SS6.5.4 wire tier): the gateway matches the requested model against the\nthree CONFIGURED tier models. A match runs AND meters at THAT tier (FAST/WORKHORSE/EXPERT) with the\nclient's thinking/output_config preserved (a trailing '[1m]' client alias is stripped on the wire).\nAny OTHER model string keeps the historical behavior: clamp to FAST + strip reasoning params.\nMotivation: Agent-SDK subprocess traffic rides this gateway via ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL - the always-FAST\nclamp silently degraded chat/build/planner to the FAST model (strict-JSON planning starved).\nBilling impact: matched EXPERT calls meter at 0.4 vs FAST 0.02 - correct per SS6.3, ~20x costlier.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "strokeColor": "#b45309",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 400528108,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 524480560,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "groupIds": [],
      "boundElements": null,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "containerId": null,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "rawText": "AS-BUILT amendment 2026-07-11 (SS6.5.4 wire tier): the gateway matches the requested model against the\nthree CONFIGURED tier models. A match runs AND meters at THAT tier (FAST/WORKHORSE/EXPERT) with the\nclient's thinking/output_config preserved (a trailing '[1m]' client alias is stripped on the wire).\nAny OTHER model string keeps the historical behavior: clamp to FAST + strip reasoning params.\nMotivation: Agent-SDK subprocess traffic rides this gateway via ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL - the always-FAST\nclamp silently degraded chat/build/planner to the FAST model (strict-JSON planning starved).\nBilling impact: matched EXPERT calls meter at 0.4 vs FAST 0.02 - correct per SS6.3, ~20x costlier."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "s1-heartbeat-note",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 960,
      "width": 734.4,
      "height": 87.5,
      "text": "S1 heartbeat-and-replay 2026-07-17: stream:true commits the SSE 200 after auth+allowance (401/402 stay clean\nHTTP), pings {\"type\": \"ping\"} every 15 s while the BUFFERED upstream call runs, then replays the detokenized\nSSE body VERBATIM in one write. Post-commitment failures arrive as ONE in-stream 'error' event (upstream JSON\nre-emitted; cap trip -> rate_limit_error; credential death -> api_error). Transport stays buffered -\nanonymisation outranks streaming. Provider headers not forwarded in stream mode.",
      "originalText": "S1 heartbeat-and-replay 2026-07-17: stream:true commits the SSE 200 after auth+allowance (401/402 stay clean\nHTTP), pings {\"type\": \"ping\"} every 15 s while the BUFFERED upstream call runs, then replays the detokenized\nSSE body VERBATIM in one write. Post-commitment failures arrive as ONE in-stream 'error' event (upstream JSON\nre-emitted; cap trip -> rate_limit_error; credential death -> api_error). Transport stays buffered -\nanonymisation outranks streaming. Provider headers not forwarded in stream mode.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "strokeColor": "#b45309",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 71717171,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 71717172,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "groupIds": [],
      "boundElements": null,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "containerId": null,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "rawText": "S1 heartbeat-and-replay 2026-07-17: stream:true commits the SSE 200 after auth+allowance (401/402 stay clean\nHTTP), pings {\"type\": \"ping\"} every 15 s while the BUFFERED upstream call runs, then replays the detokenized\nSSE body VERBATIM in one write. Post-commitment failures arrive as ONE in-stream 'error' event (upstream JSON\nre-emitted; cap trip -> rate_limit_error; credential death -> api_error). Transport stays buffered -\nanonymisation outranks streaming. Provider headers not forwarded in stream mode.",
      "updated": 1784274879089
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "s2-family-map-note",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 1071.5,
      "width": 734.4,
      "height": 87.5,
      "text": "S2 family mapping 2026-07-17: tier resolution is now exact configured-tier match -> model-FAMILY match\n(opus->EXPERT, sonnet->WORKHORSE, haiku->FAST; case/dated/[1m]-tolerant) -> FAST clamp. thinking/\noutput_config travel on any exact OR family match and are stripped only on the clamp; the wire model is\nalways the configured tier model. /models now lists all three tiers. Stock Claude Code ids land on real\ntiers instead of exact-missing into FAST with thinking stripped.",
      "originalText": "S2 family mapping 2026-07-17: tier resolution is now exact configured-tier match -> model-FAMILY match\n(opus->EXPERT, sonnet->WORKHORSE, haiku->FAST; case/dated/[1m]-tolerant) -> FAST clamp. thinking/\noutput_config travel on any exact OR family match and are stripped only on the clamp; the wire model is\nalways the configured tier model. /models now lists all three tiers. Stock Claude Code ids land on real\ntiers instead of exact-missing into FAST with thinking stripped.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "strokeColor": "#b45309",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
