      "containerId": null,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "rawText": "S2 family mapping 2026-07-17: tier resolution is now exact configured-tier match -> model-FAMILY match\n(opus->EXPERT, sonnet->WORKHORSE, haiku->FAST; case/dated/[1m]-tolerant) -> FAST clamp. thinking/\noutput_config travel on any exact OR family match and are stripped only on the clamp; the wire model is\nalways the configured tier model. /models now lists all three tiers. Stock Claude Code ids land on real\ntiers instead of exact-missing into FAST with thinking stripped.",
      "updated": 1784277018642
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "s3-count-tokens-note",
      "x": 60,
      "y": 1183.0,
      "width": 734.4,
      "height": 87.5,
      "text": "S3 count_tokens 2026-07-17: POST /v1/messages/count_tokens (+ /messages alias) forwards through the\nchokepoint - full anonymisation posture, S2 tier resolution (honest counts), 401 refresh-retry - but\nNEVER billed, NEVER rate-capped, allowance-exempt (free upstream; Claude Code polls it continuously).\nBody-limit fix: the global 1 MB parser skips /api/v1/llm, the gateway's own 50 MB parser is live, and\ngateway parse errors answer in the Anthropic error shape (413/400 invalid_request_error).",
      "originalText": "S3 count_tokens 2026-07-17: POST /v1/messages/count_tokens (+ /messages alias) forwards through the\nchokepoint - full anonymisation posture, S2 tier resolution (honest counts), 401 refresh-retry - but\nNEVER billed, NEVER rate-capped, allowance-exempt (free upstream; Claude Code polls it continuously).\nBody-limit fix: the global 1 MB parser skips /api/v1/llm, the gateway's own 50 MB parser is live, and\ngateway parse errors answer in the Anthropic error shape (413/400 invalid_request_error).",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "strokeColor": "#b45309",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
